WEBVTT

00:03.320 --> 00:05.070
_

00:05.076 --> 00:06.700
May 6th.

00:06.702 --> 00:07.968
It's about to begin.

00:07.970 --> 00:10.371
Whose name was on the account?

00:10.373 --> 00:13.374
[gunshots]

00:13.376 --> 00:15.242
It was yours, Link.

00:15.244 --> 00:17.144
You planted that message.

00:17.146 --> 00:18.793
How does it feel to know
that you're responsible

00:18.795 --> 00:20.072
for the death of your friend?

00:20.283 --> 00:22.891
The Machine gave up its location
to save our lives.

00:23.052 --> 00:25.453
They're going to kill her,
Harold.

00:29.194 --> 00:32.628
[grunting]

00:36.634 --> 00:37.868
[car horn honks]

00:37.870 --> 00:41.037
[subdued music]

00:41.039 --> 00:43.473
♪

00:43.475 --> 00:45.776
(news anchor) An update
now on our top story.

00:45.778 --> 00:47.510
Utilities have yet to determine

00:47.512 --> 00:49.445
what is behind
these power surges.

00:49.447 --> 00:52.982
Although, speculation ranges
from aging infrastructure

00:52.984 --> 00:55.084
to Chinese hackers.

00:55.086 --> 00:56.519
- Samaritan.
- Indeed.

00:56.521 --> 00:57.987
It appears to have located
the Machine.

00:57.989 --> 01:00.323
Most likely on a data farm
out West.

01:00.325 --> 01:03.793
But the surges are happening
all over, now headed East.

01:03.795 --> 01:05.761
It's possible that the Machine
has distributed itself

01:05.763 --> 01:07.262
in more than one place.

01:07.264 --> 01:09.832
Samaritan's trying to
cut off Her power.

01:09.834 --> 01:11.333
Starve Her.
And for all we know,

01:11.335 --> 01:12.668
it's already succeeded.

01:12.670 --> 01:14.369
Still no word from the Machine?

01:14.371 --> 01:17.372
Not since Greer let us go.

01:17.374 --> 01:20.375
She won't talk to me.
Or can't.

01:20.377 --> 01:23.312
[phone ringing]

01:28.617 --> 01:30.352
It's coming from
behind the wall.

01:30.354 --> 01:33.989
[suspenseful music]

01:33.991 --> 01:35.057
[grunts]

01:35.059 --> 01:36.123
[phone ringing]

01:36.125 --> 01:38.693
♪

01:38.695 --> 01:39.794
[grunting]

01:39.796 --> 01:41.729
[phone ringing]

01:41.731 --> 01:43.965
♪

01:43.967 --> 01:46.968
[phone ringing]

01:46.970 --> 01:50.171
Must have been walled in
during renovation decades ago.

01:50.173 --> 01:51.873
(the Machine)
0. 0. 0. 0.

01:51.875 --> 01:53.240
What is it?

01:53.242 --> 01:54.842
- Nine zeros.
- 0. 0. 0. 0. 0.

01:54.844 --> 01:56.643
It's the Machine's
distress code.

01:56.645 --> 01:59.480
I programmed it in to warn me
of an imminent system shutdown.

01:59.482 --> 02:01.515
- 0. 0. 0. 0. 0.
- Shutdown?

02:01.517 --> 02:03.250
- You mean--
- The Machine is dying,

02:03.252 --> 02:05.886
Ms. Groves.

02:05.888 --> 02:07.355
(the Machine)
3. 1. 4.

02:07.357 --> 02:10.190
- 3-1-4...
- Pi.

02:10.192 --> 02:11.892
That's the code for the Case.
She needs our help.

02:11.894 --> 02:14.962
[suspenseful music]

02:14.964 --> 02:17.931
♪

02:17.933 --> 02:19.766
How can we help the Machine
if we don't know where it is?

02:19.768 --> 02:23.837
She needs us to pick up a few
more things, and fast.

02:23.839 --> 02:25.238
We'll find Her on the way.

02:25.240 --> 02:27.440
Mr. Reese isn't answering
his phone.

02:27.442 --> 02:28.674
A mission this critical,
shouldn't we try to find him,

02:28.676 --> 02:30.510
bring him along?

02:30.512 --> 02:32.245
You want to stay here and wait
for the phone to ring, Harold?

02:32.247 --> 02:35.648
Fine. But right now,
we have another calling.

02:35.650 --> 02:39.152
♪

02:43.223 --> 02:45.958
Time to make a deal,
Detective Riley.

02:45.960 --> 02:48.561
The Elias era is over.

02:48.563 --> 02:51.096
New World Order.

02:51.098 --> 02:54.266
I want the same arrangement
he had.

02:54.268 --> 02:57.770
Your friend Harold
is gonna be my inside man.

02:57.772 --> 03:00.605
I want the keys to the city.

03:00.607 --> 03:03.742
There are no keys.

03:03.744 --> 03:06.412
No arrangements.

03:06.414 --> 03:09.148
- You think I'm stupid?
- No.

03:09.150 --> 03:13.385
You're just smart enough
to get yourself killed.

03:13.387 --> 03:15.486
Go get Detective Fusco.

03:15.488 --> 03:17.989
Put a bullet in his head.

03:17.991 --> 03:21.059
[dramatic music]

03:21.061 --> 03:28.934
♪

03:31.470 --> 03:33.171
Here I thought you couldn't
look any worse.

03:33.173 --> 03:36.340
You should see
the other guy's knuckles.

03:36.342 --> 03:37.641
Yeah.

03:37.643 --> 03:40.711
[suspenseful music]

03:40.713 --> 03:41.979
♪

03:41.981 --> 03:45.616
[both panting]

03:45.618 --> 03:47.285
That was kind of hot.

03:47.287 --> 03:48.351
Let's go, champ.

03:48.353 --> 03:56.226
♪

04:00.465 --> 04:03.266
Zachary, how goes the hunt?

04:03.268 --> 04:04.767
(Zachary) Nearly a quarter
of the nation's power supply

04:04.769 --> 04:06.169
has been compromised.

04:06.171 --> 04:09.106
Soon the Machine will lose
access to it entirely.

04:09.108 --> 04:13.477
We've all but treed the fox,
Mr. Greer.

04:13.479 --> 04:16.113
[power lines buzzing]

04:16.115 --> 04:17.714
Splendid.

04:17.716 --> 04:20.483
Then burn down the tree.

04:28.894 --> 04:31.127
[dramatic music] _

04:31.129 --> 04:33.329
♪

04:33.331 --> 04:36.365
Shiffman, index these numbers
with addresses.

04:36.367 --> 04:37.366
Coordinates.

04:37.368 --> 04:39.868
We're looking for a target.

04:39.870 --> 04:42.238
Threat reports for tomorrow,
May 6th.

04:42.240 --> 04:44.240
New York, Chicago, DC.

04:44.242 --> 04:46.742
Just the highlights.

04:46.744 --> 04:49.311
Yankees game,
Empire State Building,

04:49.313 --> 04:51.247
subway system, all low.

04:51.249 --> 04:54.182
Willis Tower, Wrigley Field,
negligible.

04:54.184 --> 04:55.406
DC...

04:56.035 --> 04:57.053
_

04:57.154 --> 04:59.988
No reports for DC.

04:59.990 --> 05:01.056
None?

05:01.058 --> 05:05.761
♪

05:05.763 --> 05:06.962
There they are.

05:06.964 --> 05:08.930
All low.

05:08.932 --> 05:10.098
Must have been a glitch.

05:10.100 --> 05:11.733
Samaritan had a glitch?

05:11.735 --> 05:16.937
♪

05:16.939 --> 05:19.340
I have reason to believe
an attack is gonna take place

05:19.342 --> 05:21.709
in the next 24 hours.

05:21.711 --> 05:24.011
It's called "the Correction."

05:24.013 --> 05:25.613
May 6th, what have you heard?

05:25.615 --> 05:28.515
Any operations in and around
the capital?

05:28.517 --> 05:30.151
All quiet.

05:30.153 --> 05:34.021
Except the address
in Columbia Heights.

05:34.023 --> 05:35.389
The one in the memo.

05:35.391 --> 05:38.492
What memo?

05:38.494 --> 05:40.327
Operational quarantine.

05:40.329 --> 05:42.062
Do not disturb.
Nobody in our out.

05:42.064 --> 05:44.197
Columbia Heights?

05:44.199 --> 05:46.300
Who wrote this memo?

05:46.302 --> 05:48.935
Ma'am, you did.

05:50.000 --> 05:56.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:59.314 --> 06:01.014
[handcuffs rattling]

06:01.016 --> 06:02.882
Detective's gone.

06:02.884 --> 06:05.251
Somebody sprung him.

06:05.253 --> 06:07.320
And look who came back.

06:07.322 --> 06:08.721
Why would I help some cop?

06:08.723 --> 06:11.224
Because that's your game.

06:11.226 --> 06:13.726
(Dominic) You play both
sides of the fence.

06:13.728 --> 06:17.730
Just like you did with us
and the Cartel.

06:17.732 --> 06:19.765
Didn't think I'd ever really
trust you, did you?

06:19.767 --> 06:22.802
[ominous music]

06:22.804 --> 06:24.837
♪

06:24.839 --> 06:26.171
[grunts]

06:30.276 --> 06:31.944
I came to get answers.

06:31.946 --> 06:33.712
The only thing we're leaving
is bodies.

06:33.714 --> 06:36.915
Lock down all the exits,
find Detective Fusco,

06:36.917 --> 06:38.016
and shoot him on sight.

06:38.018 --> 06:45.891
♪

06:48.627 --> 06:50.595
(Root) She's talking
to me again, Harry.

06:50.597 --> 06:51.896
Surely, the Machine
isn't hiding itself

06:51.898 --> 06:53.465
in a high-end
apartment building.

06:53.467 --> 06:55.467
She led us here
for a reason.

06:55.469 --> 06:57.769
We just have to do what She says
when She says it.

06:57.771 --> 06:59.036
Easy for you to say.
You're the one

06:59.038 --> 07:00.438
the Machine
says everything to.

07:00.440 --> 07:01.906
I'm telling you,
there is no fire.

07:01.908 --> 07:03.207
Our alarm didn't even go off.

07:03.209 --> 07:04.942
The why did our system
say it did?

07:04.944 --> 07:06.744
(firefighter) We got
confirmation from dispatch.

07:06.746 --> 07:09.380
[suspenseful music]

07:09.382 --> 07:10.681
See, Harry?

07:10.683 --> 07:12.049
The Machine has a plan.

07:12.051 --> 07:15.452
♪

07:15.454 --> 07:16.988
[elevator dings]

07:16.990 --> 07:18.322
(Finch)
The penthouse?

07:18.324 --> 07:19.991
♪

07:19.993 --> 07:22.326
Look at these.

07:22.328 --> 07:24.795
The bleeding edge
of night vision system.

07:24.797 --> 07:27.798
Ultra HD, built-in
infrared illuminator,

07:27.800 --> 07:30.333
and piezoelectric battery
that charges itself

07:30.335 --> 07:32.436
whenever it's moved.

07:32.438 --> 07:33.970
Never run out of juice.

07:33.972 --> 07:35.038
Go ahead.

07:35.040 --> 07:39.910
♪

07:39.912 --> 07:42.312
Turn off lights.

07:42.314 --> 07:44.347
[remote beeping]

07:44.349 --> 07:47.483
♪

07:47.485 --> 07:48.518
[gunshots ring]

07:48.520 --> 07:49.585
[groaning]

07:49.587 --> 07:52.188
♪

07:52.190 --> 07:53.790
[remote beeps]

07:53.792 --> 07:55.325
Sold.

07:55.327 --> 07:57.627
We'll take 'em.

07:57.629 --> 07:59.529
Got what we came for.

07:59.531 --> 08:01.497
Come on, Harry.

08:01.499 --> 08:02.899
[grunting]

08:02.901 --> 08:06.769
♪

08:06.771 --> 08:07.870
(Finch)
Oh, dear.

08:07.872 --> 08:09.104
[gunshot ring]

08:09.106 --> 08:10.807
Why aren't we moving?

08:10.809 --> 08:12.674
New York's Bravest
down there must have disabled

08:12.676 --> 08:15.411
the emergency override.

08:15.413 --> 08:17.446
We'll have to hack the elevator,
reprogram the controls.

08:17.448 --> 08:19.714
There's no time.

08:19.716 --> 08:20.916
[gunshot rings]

08:20.918 --> 08:22.784
♪

08:22.786 --> 08:24.653
No more standing
on the sidelines.

08:24.655 --> 08:26.455
You want us to save your skin?

08:26.457 --> 08:28.557
Get in the game.

08:28.559 --> 08:31.159
♪

08:31.161 --> 08:32.226
[gunshot rings]

08:33.486 --> 08:34.629
♪ _

08:34.631 --> 08:35.730
[elevator bell dings] _

08:35.732 --> 08:36.731
[laughs softly]

08:36.732 --> 08:37.732
[elevator whirring]

08:37.734 --> 08:39.167
[gunshots ringing out]

08:39.169 --> 08:40.802
♪

08:40.804 --> 08:42.303
Thank you. _

08:42.304 --> 08:43.304
[bell dings]

08:43.306 --> 08:45.073
Get ready, Harry.

08:45.075 --> 08:48.009
Something tells me this won't be
our last wild ride today.

08:50.668 --> 08:53.552
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

09:01.115 --> 09:03.282
(Root) The Machine wants us
to break into Caleb's office

09:03.284 --> 09:04.283
and borrow a few things.

09:04.285 --> 09:07.354
[dramatic music]

09:07.356 --> 09:10.923
♪

09:10.925 --> 09:13.793
(Finch) Your employee ID got us
through the front door, Ms. Groves.

09:13.795 --> 09:18.197
But accessing the company code
will be a whole other matter.

09:18.199 --> 09:20.266
For a genius,
my boss keeps his code

09:20.268 --> 09:23.635
locked behind a surprisingly
last-gen security structure.

09:23.637 --> 09:28.040
♪

09:28.042 --> 09:29.976
The cameras are resisting loops,

09:29.978 --> 09:31.744
so I've had to
disable them entirely.

09:31.746 --> 09:34.413
Are you sure
that's such a good idea, Harry?

09:34.415 --> 09:37.949
If the Machine can't see us,
She can't help us.

09:37.951 --> 09:39.385
I found the code.

09:39.387 --> 09:44.189
Now I just need to download it.

09:44.191 --> 09:45.391
That was way too easy.

09:45.393 --> 09:48.293
[footsteps approaching]

09:48.295 --> 09:50.328
Which means...

09:50.330 --> 09:52.663
(Caleb)
Just relax guys.

09:52.665 --> 09:54.966
I'm sure there's a good reason
why Shannon, here,

09:54.968 --> 09:57.302
or whatever your name really is,

09:57.304 --> 09:58.904
broke into a secure area

09:58.906 --> 10:00.939
and tried to access
my compression algorithm.

10:00.941 --> 10:02.774
Look, I know this sounds insane,

10:02.776 --> 10:04.075
but I'm trying
to save the world,

10:04.077 --> 10:05.610
and your compression algorithm

10:05.612 --> 10:09.280
plays a small but crucial part
of doing that.

10:09.282 --> 10:12.417
I just, I can't think
why I should trust you.

10:12.419 --> 10:14.084
Then don't.

10:14.086 --> 10:15.052
Trust him.

10:15.054 --> 10:16.821
[door opens]

10:16.823 --> 10:19.690
Hello, Caleb.

10:19.692 --> 10:20.725
Mr. Swift.

10:20.727 --> 10:23.561
[laughs softly]

10:23.563 --> 10:25.162
What's going on here?

10:25.164 --> 10:27.164
Let me just take a moment
to say how proud I am

10:27.166 --> 10:28.832
of everything you've done
with your life

10:28.834 --> 10:30.700
since I knew you
as a student.

10:30.702 --> 10:33.870
And I truly wish there were time
here for a more appropriate

10:33.872 --> 10:36.941
and meaningful reunion,
but right now,

10:36.943 --> 10:39.143
I have to try to explain
as best I can

10:39.145 --> 10:42.345
why we need your algorithm.

10:42.347 --> 10:43.647
Hold on, Mr. Swift.

10:43.649 --> 10:46.683
♪

10:46.685 --> 10:48.318
[typing]

10:50.433 --> 10:52.298
_

10:54.158 --> 10:56.827
Anything you need,
you can have.

10:56.829 --> 10:59.262
No explanation necessary.

10:59.264 --> 11:00.430
You saved my life.

11:00.432 --> 11:07.170
♪

11:07.172 --> 11:08.704
Thank you.

11:08.706 --> 11:11.341
Boys, there's no time.

11:11.343 --> 11:12.976
Oh, and Caleb,
we also borrowed

11:12.978 --> 11:15.678
a few of the prototype 128 gig
multi-state RAM chips

11:15.680 --> 11:17.880
from Project X.

11:17.882 --> 11:20.716
You knew about Project X?

11:20.718 --> 11:22.651
Really needed it.

11:22.653 --> 11:23.853
Thanks again.

11:23.855 --> 11:29.692
♪

11:30.794 --> 11:33.862
[suspenseful music]

11:33.864 --> 11:39.167
♪

11:39.169 --> 11:41.870
[phone beeping]

11:41.872 --> 11:43.472
Huh.

11:43.474 --> 11:45.440
Look what we have here.

11:45.442 --> 11:48.109
A phone hooked up
to my mesh network.

11:48.111 --> 11:52.313
Detective Riley and company
commandeered it for themselves.

11:52.315 --> 11:55.750
Clearly, you owe me a big favor.

11:55.752 --> 11:57.519
[door opens]

11:57.521 --> 11:58.520
[footsteps approaching]

11:58.522 --> 12:00.388
[door closes]

12:00.390 --> 12:02.490
We got a soldier down,
south exit.

12:02.492 --> 12:04.025
No radio response.

12:04.027 --> 12:05.359
We got to move out.

12:05.361 --> 12:07.061
That is quite a dilemma.

12:07.063 --> 12:11.332
You stay and be caught,
or leave empty-handed.

12:11.334 --> 12:13.067
Unlock it.

12:13.069 --> 12:17.338
Get Harold down here,
or both their lives are on you.

12:17.340 --> 12:18.605
[guns cocking]

12:18.607 --> 12:24.011
♪

12:24.013 --> 12:26.112
I won't ask again.

12:26.114 --> 12:28.114
♪

12:30.552 --> 12:32.553
Perhaps if we knew
the Machine's location,

12:32.555 --> 12:34.988
we could determine how much time
we have to save it.

12:34.990 --> 12:36.757
Clearly, the Machine
is experiencing

12:36.759 --> 12:40.826
some kind of malfunction brought
on by these power surges.

12:40.828 --> 12:42.762
So far,
all we've gathered to save it

12:42.764 --> 12:45.231
is one algorithm,
a few RAM chips,

12:45.233 --> 12:47.333
and a pair of
night-vision goggles.

12:47.335 --> 12:49.335
(Finch)
Hardly a recipe for success.

12:49.337 --> 12:52.605
Recipe? We're not baking
a cake here, Harold.

12:52.607 --> 12:53.739
(Root)
Trust the process.

12:53.741 --> 12:58.510
[phone ringing]

12:58.512 --> 13:00.312
Mr. Reese, what a relief
to finally hear from--

13:00.314 --> 13:01.881
(Dominic)
Mr. Reese?

13:01.883 --> 13:03.783
Of course.

13:03.785 --> 13:06.351
I figured Riley
wasn't his real name.

13:06.353 --> 13:08.187
Nice to meet you, Harold.

13:08.189 --> 13:10.189
(Dominic) Can't wait to
start working together.

13:10.191 --> 13:11.523
Where is John?

13:11.525 --> 13:13.225
(Dominic)
Don't worry about John.

13:13.227 --> 13:17.129
As long as you cooperate,
he gets to keep on breathing.

13:17.131 --> 13:18.263
(Dominic)
We'll send you a new location.

13:18.265 --> 13:20.065
Be there in 15.

13:20.067 --> 13:21.366
Alone.

13:21.368 --> 13:23.469
[phones beeping]

13:23.471 --> 13:25.904
The Machine will have to wait.
I have to go help John.

13:25.906 --> 13:28.640
Harold, the Machine
is the priority here.

13:28.642 --> 13:31.042
No, people are the priority
here, Ms. Groves.

13:31.044 --> 13:34.112
The Machine's only reason
for existing is to save them.

13:34.114 --> 13:36.915
I'm not gonna sacrifice John
to help rescue an AI

13:36.917 --> 13:39.417
that on its best days is
cryptic and withholding,

13:39.419 --> 13:41.886
and on its worst,
borderline homicidal.

13:41.888 --> 13:43.921
She's not perfect, Harold.

13:43.923 --> 13:48.292
But She's the only chance
we've got.

13:48.294 --> 13:50.060
We let Sameen slip away.

13:50.062 --> 13:52.796
So now we're supposed to
let John go, too?

13:52.798 --> 13:55.199
I don't want to sacrifice
Sameen, either.

13:55.201 --> 13:57.602
But if the Machine dies,
the world we wake up in tomorrow

13:57.604 --> 14:00.337
is one none of us wants to see.

14:00.339 --> 14:03.306
She needs John alive
as much as we do.

14:03.308 --> 14:05.009
She won't let him down.

14:05.011 --> 14:06.409
Come on.

14:06.411 --> 14:09.479
[dramatic music]

14:09.481 --> 14:11.481
♪

14:11.483 --> 14:15.986
Come on, jump in the car.

14:15.988 --> 14:17.820
Are you out of your mind?

14:17.822 --> 14:19.523
Since when is that relevant?

14:19.525 --> 14:20.590
Get in, Harry.

14:20.592 --> 14:23.436
♪

14:26.290 --> 14:28.834
_

14:29.233 --> 14:32.669
Looks like
we found our Harold.

14:32.671 --> 14:36.505
Which means you
are no longer needed.

14:36.507 --> 14:38.107
Nor you.

14:38.109 --> 14:39.542
Put them down.

14:39.544 --> 14:41.544
(Dominic)
Let's get the hell out of here.

14:41.546 --> 14:43.946
Mr. Reese comes with us.

14:43.948 --> 14:45.614
[beeping]

14:45.616 --> 14:47.483
What the hell is that?

14:47.485 --> 14:50.719
Old fax machine.

14:50.721 --> 14:55.457
What does it say?

14:55.459 --> 14:58.194
"Sharp right leg.
Left knee, ACL.

14:58.196 --> 15:00.296
Tactical blade.
Glass jaw."

15:00.298 --> 15:02.698
[dramatic music]

15:02.700 --> 15:04.633
[grunting]

15:04.635 --> 15:07.302
[fighting]

15:07.304 --> 15:08.636
[grunting]

15:08.638 --> 15:09.705
(the Machine)
Can. You. Hear. Me?

15:09.707 --> 15:10.739
Hell yes.

15:10.741 --> 15:12.640
(the Machine)
10:00.

15:12.642 --> 15:13.641
[gunshots ringing]

15:13.643 --> 15:14.976
(the Machine)
3:00.

15:14.978 --> 15:15.977
[gunshots ringing]

15:15.979 --> 15:17.312
(the Machine)
1:00.

15:17.314 --> 15:18.379
[groaning]

15:18.381 --> 15:22.050
♪

15:22.052 --> 15:23.050
(male officer)
Drop the gun!

15:23.052 --> 15:24.519
Get down!

15:24.521 --> 15:26.987
I said down on the ground!

15:26.989 --> 15:27.988
All clear.

15:27.990 --> 15:30.891
We got him, Detective.

15:30.893 --> 15:32.893
Detective Fusco.

15:32.895 --> 15:34.529
You're under arrest, jackass.

15:34.531 --> 15:37.465
[heroic music]

15:42.670 --> 15:44.338
(Grice)
Quarantined address.

15:44.340 --> 15:45.539
Columbia Heights.

15:45.541 --> 15:47.942
(Control)
Get the ratchet.

15:47.944 --> 15:50.945
[alarm ringing]

15:50.947 --> 15:54.014
[suspenseful music]

15:54.016 --> 15:56.283
♪

15:56.285 --> 15:58.084
Takes some balls
to run an off-the-books op

15:58.086 --> 16:01.355
at a quarantined address.
So why'd you choose me?

16:01.357 --> 16:04.224
You had Agent Shaw in your
sights and you let her go.

16:04.226 --> 16:06.426
You value people over protocol.

16:06.428 --> 16:08.629
And you're not afraid
to question authority.

16:08.631 --> 16:10.364
[grunts]

16:10.366 --> 16:13.233
Well then,
I have another question.

16:13.235 --> 16:15.034
Why are we breaking into
this place?

16:15.036 --> 16:17.103
That quarantine order
from Research?

16:17.105 --> 16:18.972
(Grice)
Mm-hmm.

16:18.974 --> 16:20.807
I never ordered it.

16:20.809 --> 16:21.875
(Control)
That's why.

16:21.877 --> 16:24.944
[suspenseful music]

16:24.946 --> 16:26.880
♪

16:26.882 --> 16:29.047
[sniffs]
That smell.

16:29.049 --> 16:30.283
Ammonium nitrate.

16:30.285 --> 16:31.651
Fertilizer.

16:31.653 --> 16:33.419
From the smell, a lot of it
was here.

16:33.421 --> 16:35.288
Just a few hours ago.

16:35.290 --> 16:37.390
Blueprints, too.

16:37.392 --> 16:39.124
But for what?

16:39.126 --> 16:43.596
(Grice)
Ma'am, you need to see this.

16:43.598 --> 16:45.130
Propane tank.

16:45.132 --> 16:47.833
Why is the lid cut off?

16:47.835 --> 16:51.003
To build a bomb.

16:51.005 --> 16:53.172
(Control) There's at least
a half a dozen more.

16:53.174 --> 16:56.308
Enough to blow an entire floor
of a federal building.

16:56.310 --> 16:58.310
And whoever made it

16:58.312 --> 17:00.867
is already on the move.

17:11.550 --> 17:13.884
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

17:13.886 --> 17:18.855
[indistinct chatter]

17:18.857 --> 17:21.258
Take care of yourself, John.

17:21.260 --> 17:23.426
I'm gonna enjoy watching you
get put away.

17:23.429 --> 17:27.564
I wouldn't count those chickens
just yet.

17:27.566 --> 17:28.932
I'm gonna go along for the ride.

17:28.934 --> 17:30.700
Make sure the Feds
don't screw this one up.

17:30.702 --> 17:31.868
Want to jump in the van?

17:31.870 --> 17:33.403
I'll take a rain check.

17:33.405 --> 17:35.739
I need to help Finch.

17:35.741 --> 17:36.740
You did a nice job, Lionel.

17:36.742 --> 17:39.809
[heroic music]

17:39.811 --> 17:45.615
♪

17:45.617 --> 17:46.616
[door closes]

17:46.618 --> 17:49.686
[ominous music]

17:49.688 --> 17:54.390
♪

17:54.392 --> 17:56.392
I fail to see how
over a dozen bags of ice

17:56.394 --> 17:58.194
plays into
our larger mission.

17:58.196 --> 17:59.762
It's Cinco De Mayo.

17:59.764 --> 18:02.298
If She asks us to pick up
some salt and limes,

18:02.300 --> 18:03.633
I'd say you have your answer.

18:03.635 --> 18:05.401
Which brings me
to my next concern.

18:05.403 --> 18:07.302
You've been in God Mode
since this morning.

18:07.304 --> 18:09.304
Isn't such constant contact
with the Machine

18:09.306 --> 18:11.573
likely to attract
Samaritan's attention?

18:11.575 --> 18:14.810
[tires screeching]

18:14.812 --> 18:17.245
When you're right, Harry,
you're right. Start the car.

18:17.247 --> 18:20.415
Hey, you're five bucks short
on the ice.

18:20.417 --> 18:22.551
Whoa!
We're cool, we're cool.

18:22.553 --> 18:25.820
Appreciate your understanding.

18:25.822 --> 18:28.557
[gunshots]

18:28.559 --> 18:29.558
Get in!

18:29.560 --> 18:30.559
[gunshots]

18:30.561 --> 18:32.760
[suspenseful music]

18:32.762 --> 18:35.697
[gunshots]

18:38.401 --> 18:41.335
(news reporter) With the wave of
brownouts spreading across the US,

18:41.337 --> 18:44.706
experts expect power surges
and outages of the East Coast

18:44.708 --> 18:46.207
and into the greater
New York area.

18:48.844 --> 18:51.779
[electricity buzzing]

18:53.781 --> 18:56.183
Management's been redirecting
everyone.

18:56.185 --> 18:58.719
There have been surges
all over the country.

18:58.721 --> 19:00.888
We're gonna be banking
some serious OT tonight.

19:00.890 --> 19:04.424
What the hell are you doing?

19:04.426 --> 19:06.927
We've been replacing these
things for how many months now?

19:06.929 --> 19:08.662
You've never been tempted
to see what's inside?

19:08.664 --> 19:10.631
It's a line conditioning box.

19:10.633 --> 19:13.299
(senior lineman) That's all you need to know.
Now put it back.

19:13.301 --> 19:15.135
But why aren't we allowed
to see what's inside?

19:15.137 --> 19:16.903
(lineman) I mean, what's
the worst that can happen?

19:16.905 --> 19:20.407
The last guy who had your job,
he opened up one of those boxes.

19:20.409 --> 19:21.908
(senior lineman)
Next day, he was gone.

19:21.910 --> 19:23.843
That's all I know.

19:27.415 --> 19:28.714
You're the boss.

19:28.716 --> 19:30.917
Smart.
Now get in the cab.

19:32.686 --> 19:35.755
[dramatic music] _

19:35.757 --> 19:38.625
♪

19:41.161 --> 19:44.564
- Senator.
- Why the urgent meeting?

19:44.566 --> 19:46.165
Your phone.

19:46.167 --> 19:49.235
[dark music]

19:49.237 --> 19:51.748
♪

19:52.931 --> 19:54.300
_

19:54.608 --> 19:56.108
Soundproofed.

19:56.110 --> 19:58.944
[chuckles]
Job finally getting to you?

19:58.946 --> 20:00.612
Not the job.

20:00.614 --> 20:02.514
Samaritan.

20:02.516 --> 20:05.116
We need to pull the feeds,
blind the damn thing, now.

20:05.118 --> 20:07.852
Why would we blind
the single greatest watchdog

20:07.854 --> 20:09.187
America has ever had?

20:09.189 --> 20:11.222
Greer used us.

20:11.224 --> 20:12.857
He's making a power play.

20:12.859 --> 20:15.560
And Samaritan is his weapon.

20:15.562 --> 20:19.330
There's gonna be a bomb
that detonates here in DC

20:19.332 --> 20:20.898
tomorrow.

20:20.900 --> 20:24.569
Why would Greer allow an attack,
much less plan one?

20:24.571 --> 20:26.137
It would make Samaritan
look inept.

20:26.139 --> 20:27.572
(Control)
Come on, Ross.

20:27.574 --> 20:29.807
You know how the wheels spin
in this city.

20:29.809 --> 20:31.642
A few pawns get fired,

20:31.644 --> 20:33.644
but the person
who's really responsible

20:33.646 --> 20:36.546
just gets a bigger checkbook.

20:36.548 --> 20:41.151
After the Vigilance attack,
<i>we</i> handed the feeds to Greer

20:41.153 --> 20:43.053
for Samaritan.

20:43.055 --> 20:46.724
After this attack, we'll be
under their thumb completely.

20:46.726 --> 20:48.759
All of us, even you.

20:48.761 --> 20:50.060
What's the alternative?

20:50.062 --> 20:51.695
Go back to the old Machine.

20:51.697 --> 20:53.930
Ingram's Machine?

20:53.932 --> 20:57.734
The black box so slippery it
moved itself to God knows where?

20:57.736 --> 20:59.402
It never lied.

20:59.404 --> 21:00.903
Never slaughtered.

21:00.905 --> 21:02.606
This meeting is over.

21:02.608 --> 21:04.774
And if you're lucky,
I won't tell anyone

21:04.776 --> 21:09.779
about the insane rant
I just heard.

21:09.781 --> 21:10.780
My phone.

21:10.782 --> 21:13.850
[dark music]

21:13.852 --> 21:14.784
♪

21:14.786 --> 21:16.385
Take my advice.

21:16.387 --> 21:17.520
Get a firm grip.

21:17.522 --> 21:20.456
♪

21:20.458 --> 21:22.291
[door opens, closes]

21:22.293 --> 21:25.227
♪

21:25.229 --> 21:27.363
[beeping] _

21:27.365 --> 21:31.033
Good advice, Senator.

21:31.035 --> 21:32.901
That's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

21:32.902 --> 21:34.562
_

21:41.077 --> 21:43.611
Iris, we need to talk.

21:43.613 --> 21:47.415
John, what's going on?

21:47.417 --> 21:49.084
You need to go now.

21:49.086 --> 21:50.451
Get out of town
for a few days.

21:50.453 --> 21:52.320
What?

21:52.322 --> 21:56.224
You once said you were
pretty sure I wasn't a cop.

21:56.226 --> 21:58.993
Well, if what I'm about to do
goes sideways,

21:58.995 --> 22:01.896
the wrong people will figure
that out, too.

22:01.898 --> 22:04.265
And anyone I care about
will be at risk.

22:04.267 --> 22:06.901
What is it,
and organized crime thing?

22:06.903 --> 22:09.837
Much worse than that.

22:09.839 --> 22:12.106
Look, I don't know how
this is gonna shake out,

22:12.108 --> 22:13.508
but you've got to trust me.

22:13.510 --> 22:15.442
You want me to trust you?

22:15.444 --> 22:16.944
Trust me.

22:16.946 --> 22:20.314
Tell me what the hell's
going on.

22:20.316 --> 22:22.817
All right.

22:22.819 --> 22:26.187
I make it through this
in one piece, we'll talk.

22:26.189 --> 22:28.488
I'll tell you everything.

22:28.490 --> 22:32.092
No holding back.

22:32.094 --> 22:33.694
Okay.

22:33.696 --> 22:36.863
John, am I going to lose you?

22:36.865 --> 22:39.899
[poignant music]

22:39.901 --> 22:42.869
♪

22:42.871 --> 22:44.571
Take care of yourself.

22:44.573 --> 22:47.708
♪

22:52.112 --> 22:55.013
Senator Garrison,
I hope you haven't summoned me

22:55.015 --> 22:57.483
for a tour of operations.

22:57.485 --> 22:59.785
If we want to see
Samaritan at work,

22:59.787 --> 23:02.488
there are more
appropriate times.

23:02.490 --> 23:03.989
Where is everyone?

23:03.991 --> 23:06.825
[dramatic music]

23:06.827 --> 23:08.460
(Control)
I gave them the night off.

23:08.462 --> 23:09.995
Cinco De Mayo.

23:09.997 --> 23:11.897
Good for morale.

23:11.899 --> 23:14.332
(Control) I told them to get a
margarita, but stay on call.

23:14.334 --> 23:18.703
Because an attack can happen
at any time.

23:18.705 --> 23:19.772
Isn't that right?

23:19.774 --> 23:23.909
♪

23:23.911 --> 23:25.176
She just gave me
our final destination.

23:25.178 --> 23:27.245
She's in Brooklyn.

23:27.247 --> 23:29.681
We're running out of time,
Harry.

23:29.683 --> 23:31.750
We can only go just so fast,
Ms. Groves.

23:31.752 --> 23:33.385
This thing has eight cylinders.

23:33.387 --> 23:35.320
But I sincerely doubt
it can fly.

23:35.322 --> 23:36.554
We'll never make it
under an hour.

23:36.556 --> 23:37.889
Not in this traffic.

23:37.891 --> 23:39.424
What we need is a little help.

23:42.331 --> 23:44.395
[heroic music] _

23:44.397 --> 23:47.999
♪

23:48.001 --> 23:49.366
I stand corrected.

23:49.368 --> 23:50.968
Hang on.
We're coming.

23:50.970 --> 23:54.538
♪

24:05.386 --> 24:08.020
[suspenseful music]

24:08.022 --> 24:09.654
(Finch)
What is this place?

24:09.656 --> 24:11.456
I don't know, but the Machine
says we're here.

24:11.458 --> 24:12.891
Let's go.

24:12.893 --> 24:16.328
♪

24:16.330 --> 24:18.030
Heard you guys
could use some help.

24:18.032 --> 24:19.364
John.

24:19.366 --> 24:20.998
(Finch)
I'm so relieved to see you.

24:21.000 --> 24:24.001
See? The Machine's taking care
of all of us.

24:24.003 --> 24:25.470
(Root)
Now we have to return the favor.

24:25.472 --> 24:26.905
Harold?

24:26.907 --> 24:30.742
- Harold Admin?
- That would be me.

24:30.744 --> 24:33.912
Sweet. Thought I was gonna have
to take these back to the truck.

24:33.914 --> 24:35.413
Sign.

24:35.415 --> 24:38.049
15 laptops, huh?
Startup?

24:38.051 --> 24:42.686
Trying to avoid a shutdown,
actually.

24:42.688 --> 24:46.157
(Root) Let's get the ice
in before it melts.

24:46.159 --> 24:47.524
[vehicles approaching]

24:47.526 --> 24:49.726
[dramatic music]

24:49.728 --> 24:52.330
- Get inside, Harold.
- Samaritan.

24:52.332 --> 24:54.030
[tires screeching]

24:54.032 --> 24:58.101
[gunfire]

24:58.103 --> 24:59.536
What's the hold up, Harold?

24:59.538 --> 25:01.672
Some surprisingly
high-tech security.

25:01.674 --> 25:05.108
[gunfire]

25:05.110 --> 25:09.613
(both) Two, four, three,
star, seven, one--

25:09.615 --> 25:10.613
I've got this.

25:10.615 --> 25:13.049
[gunfire]

25:13.051 --> 25:16.119
[suspenseful music]

25:16.121 --> 25:18.921
♪

25:18.923 --> 25:20.256
(Root)
Cozy.

25:20.258 --> 25:23.226
An electrical substation.

25:23.228 --> 25:25.964
Hidden in the heart
of residential Brooklyn.

25:28.699 --> 25:30.766
[ominous music]

25:30.768 --> 25:34.069
You seem pretty relaxed
considering the circumstances.

25:34.071 --> 25:36.606
The way I see it,
my case hangs on the credibility

25:36.608 --> 25:39.241
of a one-time dirty cop
and a detective

25:39.243 --> 25:41.377
with ties to
an organized crime boss.

25:41.379 --> 25:42.444
Won't help you with the Feds.

25:42.446 --> 25:43.945
They'll hit you with RICO.

25:43.947 --> 25:45.914
Perhaps, but the Brotherhood
runs lock up now.

25:45.916 --> 25:47.216
I've got protection.

25:47.218 --> 25:48.884
You, on the other hand...

25:48.886 --> 25:51.487
Do you plan to make my stay
inhospitable?

25:51.489 --> 25:54.456
Something like that.
Be seeing you in Rikers.

25:54.458 --> 25:56.591
I have to admit, I admire
your certainty, Dominic,

25:56.593 --> 25:59.761
but I still have a few friends.

25:59.763 --> 26:02.764
Unfortunately for you,
I am not going to Rikers.

26:02.766 --> 26:04.132
[truck approaching]

26:04.134 --> 26:07.068
[loud crashing]

26:15.978 --> 26:19.046
[suspenseful music]

26:19.048 --> 26:21.449
♪

26:21.451 --> 26:23.584
Lock it down, Finch.

26:23.586 --> 26:25.118
[grunts]

26:25.120 --> 26:26.119
[beeping]

26:26.121 --> 26:27.955
I've got a dozen bogies.

26:27.957 --> 26:30.791
I'm guessing more
are on the way.

26:30.793 --> 26:32.993
I can't hold off
an entire army.

26:32.995 --> 26:34.828
(Reese) Laptops and ice
aren't gonna help.

26:34.830 --> 26:36.263
We need to find the Machine.

26:36.265 --> 26:38.165
(Finch)
That may prove impossible.

26:38.167 --> 26:40.767
This is one of any number
of city substations

26:40.769 --> 26:42.769
devoted to the distribution
of electricity

26:42.771 --> 26:44.404
across the southern half
of New York.

26:44.406 --> 26:46.340
The Machine can't be here

26:46.342 --> 26:48.475
because there's simply
not enough room.

26:48.477 --> 26:50.677
If the Machine's not here,
then why are we?

26:50.679 --> 26:52.512
That's what we have to find out.

26:52.514 --> 26:57.950
♪

26:57.952 --> 26:59.586
Looks like a computer I made
as a teenager.

26:59.588 --> 27:00.587
(Finch)
What is it for?

27:00.589 --> 27:02.121
(Root)
No idea.

27:02.123 --> 27:05.258
Just following orders
as fast as I can.

27:05.260 --> 27:07.093
That cable, first transformer.

27:07.095 --> 27:08.507
Hurry.

27:10.698 --> 27:12.765
(Root)
You find it, Harry?

27:12.767 --> 27:15.201
(Root) The one that steps
down to 7,200 volts.

27:15.203 --> 27:16.869
Yes.
But why on earth

27:16.871 --> 27:21.673
would we need to tap into
that much raw electricity?

27:21.675 --> 27:22.841
(Finch)
Thornhill.

27:22.843 --> 27:29.114
♪

27:29.116 --> 27:30.549
John, look out your window.

27:30.551 --> 27:33.118
On the power lines,
do you see any boxes?

27:33.120 --> 27:34.386
(Reese)
I see one.

27:34.388 --> 27:36.688
It's marked with "T."
Why?

27:36.690 --> 27:39.657
I believe I was mistaken.

27:39.659 --> 27:42.394
The Machine is here.

27:42.396 --> 27:44.896
It's here because
it's everywhere.

27:44.898 --> 27:46.464
What do you mean, Harry?

27:46.466 --> 27:47.799
Two years ago, when the Machine
moved itself,

27:47.801 --> 27:50.201
it didn't go to a data farm.

27:50.203 --> 27:52.337
It went into the wires.

27:52.339 --> 27:56.541
It uploaded itself directly into
the nation's electrical grid.

27:56.543 --> 27:59.243
But Finch, if the Machine
is everywhere,

27:59.245 --> 28:01.378
then how the hell do we save it?

28:01.380 --> 28:05.182
Good question.

28:05.184 --> 28:07.184
And I think I have the answer.

28:07.186 --> 28:10.120
[dramatic music]

28:15.160 --> 28:17.328
I'm flattered
that you went to such trouble

28:17.330 --> 28:19.196
for a private conversation.

28:19.198 --> 28:21.865
Spoofing a message
from the Senator.

28:21.867 --> 28:23.334
You could have just called.

28:23.336 --> 28:26.536
I had a feeling
your schedule was booked.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.505
Through May 6th.

28:28.507 --> 28:31.441
Yes, I know about
the "Correction."

28:31.443 --> 28:33.242
Ammonium Nitrate.

28:33.244 --> 28:36.947
Easy enough to acquire that you
could frame anyone for it.

28:36.949 --> 28:41.117
But the piece you're gonna
tell me is the target.

28:41.119 --> 28:42.786
Right now.

28:42.788 --> 28:46.255
Or you're going to shoot me.

28:46.257 --> 28:48.191
You should be so lucky.

28:48.193 --> 28:51.727
If you refuse, two men are gonna
walk through that door.

28:51.729 --> 28:53.029
One will put a black bag
over your head,

28:53.031 --> 28:55.531
and the other will zip-tie
your wrists.

28:55.533 --> 28:57.533
You will be thrown
into a hole

28:57.535 --> 28:59.902
so dark and deep

28:59.904 --> 29:02.771
that even
your precious Samaritan

29:02.773 --> 29:04.940
can't see inside.

29:04.942 --> 29:08.711
And the last thing you'll hear
is my voice saying,

29:08.713 --> 29:11.580
"This is where you belong."

29:11.582 --> 29:16.451
Even if your theory
about this attack were true,

29:16.453 --> 29:19.221
think how much
you'd stand to benefit.

29:19.223 --> 29:22.657
An even more generous
black budget.

29:22.659 --> 29:25.959
Courts will rubber-stamp
any request for surveillance

29:25.961 --> 29:27.961
you care to submit.

29:27.963 --> 29:29.330
The courts.

29:29.332 --> 29:31.332
[dramatic music]

29:31.334 --> 29:32.566
That's it.

29:32.568 --> 29:36.837
♪

29:36.839 --> 29:39.773
(Control)
That number.

29:39.775 --> 29:41.975
[typing]

29:41.977 --> 29:44.811
(Control)
It's a docket number.

29:44.813 --> 29:47.480
The Supreme Court is scheduled
to hear a case challenging

29:47.482 --> 29:50.784
the federal government's
surveillance powers tomorrow.

29:50.786 --> 29:53.587
But take out the justices,

29:53.589 --> 29:55.589
and you could stack the court
in your favor

29:55.591 --> 29:57.657
for generations to come.

29:57.659 --> 29:59.392
[scoffs]

29:59.394 --> 30:01.561
Only, it's not gonna happen.

30:01.563 --> 30:02.728
[radio clicks]

30:02.730 --> 30:04.264
- Grice?
- Ma'am?

30:04.266 --> 30:06.066
(Control)
The target is the Supreme Court.

30:06.068 --> 30:08.935
Evacuate the building.
Locate the bomb.

30:08.937 --> 30:10.002
Roger that.

30:10.004 --> 30:11.571
♪

30:11.573 --> 30:13.706
[radio clomps]

30:13.708 --> 30:17.643
Looks like the Correction
has just been canceled.

30:19.713 --> 30:21.447
(Reese)
Let me get this straight, Finch.

30:21.449 --> 30:24.850
The Machine is using
the power grid as a giant brain?

30:24.852 --> 30:26.351
Essentially.

30:26.353 --> 30:29.689
There's a tremendous amount
of unused space

30:29.691 --> 30:31.623
in copper power lines.

30:31.625 --> 30:33.892
The boxes on the lines allow
the Machine's digital signals

30:33.894 --> 30:35.860
to travel in that space.

30:35.862 --> 30:39.298
A highly complex computational
system hiding in plain sight.

30:39.300 --> 30:41.866
And now that system is being
flooded with energy.

30:41.868 --> 30:44.769
Driving the Machine across
the country to this last corner

30:44.771 --> 30:46.305
of the grid around New York.

30:46.307 --> 30:48.439
Samaritan's trying to flatline
the Machine.

30:48.441 --> 30:51.542
And we need to save Her.
Before it finishes the job.

30:51.544 --> 30:53.111
[crackling over loud speakers]

30:53.113 --> 30:55.113
(Zachary)
Attention.

30:55.115 --> 30:57.716
We'd tell you you're surrounded,
but your Machine has probably

30:57.718 --> 30:59.618
filled you in on that score.

30:59.620 --> 31:01.753
Evacuate the building
and maybe you'll live.

31:01.755 --> 31:04.054
If you're still inside
when we come through that door,

31:04.056 --> 31:06.957
that will no longer be
a possibility.

31:06.959 --> 31:09.160
(Zachary)
You decide.

31:09.162 --> 31:10.294
What's the plan?

31:10.296 --> 31:12.630
We save the Machine
by storing it.

31:12.632 --> 31:14.265
Downloading it straight off
the power lines

31:14.267 --> 31:16.767
into the Random Access Memory
in this briefcase.

31:16.769 --> 31:18.336
The Machine's gonna fit
into that briefcase?

31:18.338 --> 31:20.237
Not the entire Machine.

31:20.239 --> 31:21.805
Just the core heuristics.

31:21.807 --> 31:23.907
A strand of DNA.

31:23.909 --> 31:27.811
We use Caleb's compression
algorithm to squeeze it all in.

31:27.813 --> 31:29.947
Who says you can't put the genie
back in the bottle?

31:29.949 --> 31:31.649
(Finch)
Be careful, Ms. Groves.

31:31.651 --> 31:34.084
The process you're describing
is completely untested.

31:34.086 --> 31:35.585
Even if it does work,
the Machine will be

31:35.587 --> 31:37.287
so highly compressed
that it won't be able to

31:37.289 --> 31:39.189
process information,
or send signals,

31:39.191 --> 31:40.657
or communicate in any way.

31:40.659 --> 31:42.459
And if it doesn't work?

31:42.461 --> 31:44.594
Then the Machine
will be torn apart.

31:44.596 --> 31:46.263
Core code shredded.

31:46.265 --> 31:49.266
Irretrievable.
In short, John, we'll kill it.

31:49.268 --> 31:52.502
And then they'll kill us
and the world as we know it.

31:52.504 --> 31:54.837
At least we'll die trying.

31:54.839 --> 31:59.042
We're the Machine's last hope,
Harold.

31:59.044 --> 32:00.043
Then we'd better get to work.

32:00.045 --> 32:03.112
[dramatic music]

32:03.114 --> 32:04.547
♪

32:15.120 --> 32:17.164
[indistinct shouting] _

32:18.707 --> 32:21.741
At the Supreme Court searching
for the device now, Ma'am.

32:21.743 --> 32:23.109
(Control)
Check every room, Grice.

32:23.111 --> 32:25.044
No stone left unturned.

32:25.046 --> 32:27.546
My men will find your bomb.

32:27.548 --> 32:29.148
You know me.

32:29.150 --> 32:31.584
You're not making it
out of here alive.

32:31.586 --> 32:33.385
But you could save yourself
some complications

32:33.387 --> 32:35.554
if you tell me
who put you up to this.

32:35.556 --> 32:37.256
What they offered you.

32:37.258 --> 32:40.259
Don't you recognize an idealist
when you meet one?

32:40.261 --> 32:42.561
An idealist who wants to make
the world a better place

32:42.563 --> 32:44.630
by murdering
a few hundred people?

32:44.632 --> 32:46.398
(Greer)
Oh, no.

32:46.400 --> 32:49.435
The world has only ever been
made a better place by violence.

32:49.437 --> 32:51.069
You know that.

32:51.071 --> 32:53.639
Every leader
who ever preached peace

32:53.641 --> 32:56.842
did so guarded by armed men.

32:56.844 --> 32:59.277
One thing we can agree on,

32:59.279 --> 33:04.249
kill a few people at random,
nothing changes.

33:04.251 --> 33:05.817
(Greer)
But kill the right people...

33:05.819 --> 33:08.887
[dramatic music]

33:08.889 --> 33:13.090
♪

33:13.092 --> 33:14.359
We're gonna have to
hurry this up, Harold.

33:14.361 --> 33:15.960
We got 20 or 30 of them
out there.

33:15.962 --> 33:17.262
23 in the front, actually.

33:17.264 --> 33:19.364
Ten more approaching
from the back.

33:19.366 --> 33:23.668
Not to belabor the point,
but we're running out of time.

33:23.670 --> 33:27.205
So, if this works,
the voltage gets stepped down,

33:27.207 --> 33:29.106
passes through the demodulator,

33:29.108 --> 33:31.876
where the Machine's signal is
separated from the white noise.

33:31.878 --> 33:35.012
Compressed with Caleb's
algorithm and these laptops,

33:35.014 --> 33:37.648
and then finally, into the RAM
in this briefcase,

33:37.650 --> 33:39.817
powered by the piezoelectric
battery.

33:39.819 --> 33:41.952
Not the whole
Machine.

33:41.954 --> 33:44.221
Just enough
to rebuild it.

33:44.223 --> 33:46.790
- If...
- If we make it out of here.

33:46.792 --> 33:48.692
Sorry, Mr. Reese.
I know I was upfront

33:48.694 --> 33:50.160
about the risk
that we'd be running, but--

33:50.162 --> 33:52.362
Forget about it, Harold.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.064
There's no place I'd rather be.

33:54.066 --> 33:55.732
♪

33:58.203 --> 34:02.839
[groaning]

34:02.841 --> 34:05.208
Hey, boss.

34:05.210 --> 34:06.209
Time to get you
out of here.

34:06.211 --> 34:07.510
Yeah.

34:07.512 --> 34:09.879
[groans]

34:09.880 --> 34:12.081
[suspenseful music]

34:12.083 --> 34:13.850
Come on.

34:13.851 --> 34:14.918
[loud thud]

34:14.920 --> 34:16.252
What is it?

34:16.254 --> 34:17.320
A breach in the back entrance.

34:17.322 --> 34:19.688
Get back.

34:19.690 --> 34:22.558
[gunfire]

34:22.560 --> 34:23.559
[groans]

34:23.561 --> 34:26.262
[gunfire]

34:26.264 --> 34:27.330
Reese, where the hell are you?

34:27.331 --> 34:28.731
We're sitting ducks here.

34:28.733 --> 34:30.399
(Reese)
I know.

34:30.400 --> 34:32.900
I figured
I'd get some night air.

34:32.902 --> 34:34.270
John?

34:34.272 --> 34:37.339
[suspenseful music]

34:37.341 --> 34:41.676
♪

34:41.678 --> 34:43.212
Can you hear me?

34:43.214 --> 34:45.246
- Yes.
- Good.

34:45.248 --> 34:48.416
Now kill the lights.

34:48.418 --> 34:49.484
Hold your positions.

34:49.485 --> 34:52.920
♪

34:52.922 --> 34:55.257
[booming gunfire]

34:55.259 --> 34:56.591
Smoke grenade!

34:56.592 --> 34:58.025
[booming gunfire]

34:58.027 --> 35:00.027
[smoke diffusing]

35:00.029 --> 35:01.596
(man)
I can't see him.

35:01.598 --> 35:03.632
♪

35:03.634 --> 35:05.933
(the Machine)
1:00, 11:00.

35:05.935 --> 35:07.736
(Reese) Whatever you're gonna
do in there, Finch, do it now.

35:07.738 --> 35:09.536
[gunshots ringing]

35:09.538 --> 35:10.537
Here we go.

35:10.539 --> 35:12.940
[gunshots ringing]

35:12.942 --> 35:14.475
♪

35:14.477 --> 35:17.044
[electricity buzzing]

35:17.046 --> 35:20.381
[gunshots ringing]

35:20.383 --> 35:23.384
[heavy gunfire]

35:23.386 --> 35:26.453
[dramatic music]

35:26.455 --> 35:29.390
♪

35:29.392 --> 35:31.825
[grunts]

35:31.827 --> 35:33.827
[groans]

35:33.829 --> 35:41.701
♪

35:42.770 --> 35:44.137
- Ma'am?
- Yes?

35:44.139 --> 35:46.139
(Grice)
You're not gonna believe this.

35:46.141 --> 35:49.309
I've been through every room,
every floor, there's nothing.

35:49.311 --> 35:51.644
No explosives of any kind.

35:51.646 --> 35:54.146
You're right.
I don't believe it.

35:54.148 --> 35:55.581
[radio clicks, clatters]

35:55.583 --> 35:57.082
(Control)
Where is it?

35:57.084 --> 35:58.951
Where's the bomb, Greer?

35:58.953 --> 36:03.622
Do you really think Samaritan
would use such crude tactics?

36:03.624 --> 36:07.927
You don't take over the world
with gaudy displays of violence.

36:07.929 --> 36:12.664
Real control is surgical.

36:12.666 --> 36:15.000
Invisible.

36:15.002 --> 36:18.770
It interferes
only when necessary.

36:18.772 --> 36:23.608
(Greer) No one will question Samaritan
because no one will ever know

36:23.610 --> 36:25.109
when it has acted.

36:25.111 --> 36:28.947
[suspenseful music]

36:28.949 --> 36:33.518
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

36:33.520 --> 36:36.020
All right.

36:36.022 --> 36:37.856
Let's end this.

36:37.858 --> 36:40.791
♪

36:40.793 --> 36:42.526
(Fusco)
Put down the weapon.

36:42.528 --> 36:50.335
♪

36:50.337 --> 36:53.203
Samaritan has watched
this world for a year.

36:53.205 --> 36:56.306
It settled on a list
of corrections.

36:56.308 --> 36:58.843
Corrections that were
long overdue.

36:58.845 --> 37:00.210
Put it down, Dominic.
Now.

37:00.212 --> 37:02.813
This doesn't involve you,
Detective.

37:02.815 --> 37:03.881
That's where you're wrong.

37:03.883 --> 37:11.755
♪

37:14.425 --> 37:15.492
[gunshot]

37:15.494 --> 37:18.028
♪

37:18.030 --> 37:21.798
Get down, Detective!

37:21.800 --> 37:24.401
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

37:24.403 --> 37:25.902
[whimpers]

37:25.904 --> 37:31.408
♪

37:31.410 --> 37:34.677
Most of humanity is docile.

37:34.679 --> 37:36.078
Pliant.

37:36.080 --> 37:38.080
It's only
over a few hundred people

37:38.082 --> 37:41.785
who create
all of the problems.

37:41.787 --> 37:44.787
Samaritan has identified them.

37:44.789 --> 37:46.555
(Greer)
The disruptors.

37:46.557 --> 37:51.394
The outliers who have
problems with authority.

37:51.396 --> 37:54.263
And then there's the disloyal.

37:54.265 --> 37:58.367
The grit in the gears.

37:58.369 --> 38:01.102
Thank you for leading us
directly to them.

38:01.104 --> 38:03.906
We couldn't have done it
without you...

38:03.908 --> 38:05.941
Control.

38:05.943 --> 38:07.375
[gunshots]

38:07.377 --> 38:08.376
[groans]

38:08.378 --> 38:09.945
(the Machine)
6:00

38:09.947 --> 38:11.747
- 1:00.
- [groans]

38:11.749 --> 38:12.815
- 11:00.
- [grunts]

38:12.817 --> 38:15.283
[dramatic music]

38:15.285 --> 38:18.286
[electricity buzzing]

38:18.288 --> 38:20.655
I'm gonna keep trying to
hold them off, Harold.

38:20.657 --> 38:21.722
How much longer?

38:21.724 --> 38:23.091
I don't have any idea.

38:23.093 --> 38:25.060
[gunfire]

38:25.062 --> 38:26.094
Cover your eyes.

38:26.096 --> 38:27.295
[explodes]

38:27.297 --> 38:32.834
[sharp ringing]

38:32.836 --> 38:35.837
[Pink Floyd's
Welcome To The Machine playing]

38:35.839 --> 38:40.475
♪

38:40.477 --> 38:43.754
_

38:44.080 --> 38:48.682
♪ welcome to the machine ♪

38:48.684 --> 38:50.647
_

38:50.648 --> 38:54.703
_

38:54.991 --> 38:55.922
♪ where have you been ♪

38:55.924 --> 38:58.392
We haven't failed yet.

38:58.851 --> 39:01.739
_

39:03.219 --> 39:05.365
_

39:05.367 --> 39:08.267
You had an impossible challenge.

39:08.269 --> 39:10.103
One I never programmed you for.

39:10.105 --> 39:14.210
_

39:15.999 --> 39:18.950
_

39:19.346 --> 39:21.981
That's not true...

39:21.983 --> 39:23.883
[gunshot]

39:26.594 --> 39:29.643
_

39:31.997 --> 39:34.673
_

39:37.164 --> 39:38.631
(the Machine)
11:00.

39:38.633 --> 39:40.098
[voice loses power]

39:40.100 --> 39:42.668
♪

39:42.670 --> 39:46.204
Root, I don't think the Machine
can help us anymore.

39:46.206 --> 39:47.139
♪

39:47.141 --> 39:49.575
[gunfire]

39:49.577 --> 39:51.176
She's dying.

39:51.178 --> 39:52.645
Going offline.

39:54.651 --> 39:57.215
_

39:57.217 --> 39:59.351
You were my creation.

39:59.353 --> 40:00.419
I can't let--

40:00.421 --> 40:02.587
♪

40:02.589 --> 40:04.656
I can't let you die.

40:06.036 --> 40:08.503
_

40:09.874 --> 40:12.421
_

40:12.456 --> 40:13.598
[gunfire]

40:13.600 --> 40:16.098
_

40:18.504 --> 40:23.474
[loud explosions]

40:23.476 --> 40:30.414
♪

40:30.416 --> 40:32.283
(Root)
Power's surging across the city.

40:32.285 --> 40:36.053
[electricity buzzing]

40:36.055 --> 40:38.789
(Root)
It's coming to the Machine.

40:38.791 --> 40:39.890
Harold, no!

40:39.892 --> 40:41.358
[groans]

40:41.360 --> 40:44.962
Men have gazed at the stars
for millennia

40:44.964 --> 40:47.297
and wondered whether
there was a deity up there,

40:47.299 --> 40:50.701
silently directing their fates.

40:50.703 --> 40:56.139
Today, for the first time,
they'll be right.

40:56.141 --> 40:59.142
And the world will be

40:59.144 --> 41:02.011
an undeniably better place.

41:02.013 --> 41:06.116
♪

41:06.118 --> 41:09.385
(Greer) Pity you won't
be there to see it.

41:09.387 --> 41:10.453
But the attack.

41:10.455 --> 41:17.126
_

41:17.128 --> 41:19.461
(Greer)
This was a test of loyalty.

41:19.463 --> 41:22.264
Of which, I'm sorry to say,
you failed.

41:22.266 --> 41:23.332
- [gasps]
- In Samaritan's view,

41:23.334 --> 41:25.334
there is no room for outliers.

41:25.336 --> 41:29.138
Which means there is
no room for you.

41:29.140 --> 41:30.706
But don't worry.

41:30.708 --> 41:34.876
You'll be taken to
a place where you belong.

41:34.878 --> 41:37.879
♪ welcome my son ♪

41:37.881 --> 41:38.813
♪ welcome ♪

41:38.815 --> 41:40.249
Is it finished?

41:40.251 --> 41:42.498
_

41:43.254 --> 41:44.753
♪

41:44.755 --> 41:46.655
Oh, that hurt.

41:46.657 --> 41:49.424
Did it work, Harold?

41:49.426 --> 41:52.727
Is She in there?

41:52.729 --> 41:54.663
♪ it's all right
we told you what to dream ♪

41:54.665 --> 41:56.297
Yes.

41:56.299 --> 41:57.365
Yes, I think so.

41:57.367 --> 42:01.602
♪

42:01.604 --> 42:02.971
We have to move, Harold.

42:02.973 --> 42:05.006
We're on our own now.

42:05.008 --> 42:08.509
♪

42:08.511 --> 42:09.777
[slams]

42:09.779 --> 42:17.652
♪

42:20.556 --> 42:21.722
John?

42:21.724 --> 42:23.823
♪

42:23.825 --> 42:26.893
Oh.

42:26.895 --> 42:28.728
You're alive.

42:28.730 --> 42:32.666
I got a few more years
on my pension, Harold.

42:32.668 --> 42:34.367
What's our status?

42:34.369 --> 42:38.238
Well, I've got one-and-a-half
clips, a metrocard,

42:38.240 --> 42:40.406
and God's either dead

42:40.408 --> 42:43.042
or running on double-As.

42:43.044 --> 42:46.679
You always did like a challenge,
Mr. Reese.

42:46.681 --> 42:48.014
[tires screeching]

42:48.016 --> 42:49.415
[vehicles approaching]

42:49.417 --> 42:55.688
♪

42:55.690 --> 42:56.922
Let's move.

42:56.924 --> 42:58.324
[gunfire]

42:58.326 --> 43:01.727
♪ he always ate
in the steak bar ♪

43:01.729 --> 43:05.331
♪

43:05.333 --> 43:09.000
♪ he loved to drive
in his Jaguar ♪

43:09.002 --> 43:12.104
♪

43:12.106 --> 43:18.744
♪ so welcome ♪

43:18.746 --> 43:23.215
♪ to the machine ♪

